<subSubSection id="C30198A6FFF8FFC0FCABFC69FBFB7046" pageId="4" pageNumber="117" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF8FFC0FCABFC69FC927165" blockId="4.[811,1456,1013,1327]" box="[813,888,1013,1039]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFF8FFC0FCABFB89FBFB7046" blockId="4.[811,1456,1013,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF8FFC0FCABFB89FBFF7147" author="LECOMTE H." box="[813,1045,1045,1071]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117" pagination="99 - 121" refId="ref13173" refString="LECOMTE H. 1928 a. - Ebenacees nouvelles de l'Indochine. Notulae Systematicae 4 (4): 99 - 121. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 6463259" type="journal article" year="1928">Lecomte (1928a: 104)</bibRefCitation>
cited 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF8FFC0FBD6FB89FB0F7147" box="[1104,1253,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">Poilane 13111</emphasis>
as the only original material. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFF8FFC0FC17FBA9FBB57138" author="NGUYEN T. H." box="[913,1119,1077,1104]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117" pagination="63 - 74" refId="ref13500" refString="NGUYEN T. H. 1996. - Fam. Ebenaceae Gurke, in AVERYANOV L. V., NGUYEN T. B., NGUYEN T. H., PHAN K. L., SEROV V. P. &amp; AKIMOVA G. A. (eds), Vascular Plants Synopsis of Vietnamese Flora. Russian Academy of Sciences, Saint Petersburg, Russia and National Center for Natural Sciences and Technology of Vietnam: 63 - 74." type="book chapter" year="1996">Nguyen (1996: 65)</bibRefCitation>
stated that 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF8FFC0FB51FBA9FA857127" box="[1239,1391,1077,1103]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">Poilane 13111</emphasis>
(R) is the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF8FFC0FCD3FBC9FC5E7107" box="[853,948,1109,1135]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">holotype</typeStatus>
of this species, however, no relevant collections were found at R, and this was presumably a typographical error (the correct code being P). Six sheets of 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFF8FFC0FB58FB08FA9D71C7" box="[1246,1399,1172,1199]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">Poilane 13111</emphasis>
have been located at NY, P and VNM. Among them, P00721465 bears an original label with information that matches the protologue and is well preserved. It is therefore designated here as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFF8FFC0FC21FA88FBE67046" box="[935,1036,1300,1326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="117">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
